data.enText: a group of military ships commanded by the same person
a group of ships fishing together
all the military ships of a particular country
a reduction in the size of the British fleet

data.chText: （同一机构或统一调度的）机群，车队
data.enText: a group of planes, buses, taxis, etc. travelling together or owned by the same organization
the company's new fleet of vans

means: 掠过；(船员)变换位置；消磨(时间)

tr: a group of warships organized as a tactical unit
a group of steamships operating together under the same ownership
group of motor vehicles operating together under the same ownership
group of aircraft operating together under the same ownership

example: The hummingbird flitted among the branches

value.def: A fleet is a group of ships organized to do something together, for example to fight battles or to catch fish.

example.ex: The damage inflicted upon the British fleet was devastating.
example.tran: 英国舰队遭到了毁灭性的重创。
由当地捕鱼船队供货的饭馆

value.def: A fleet of vehicles is a group of them, especially when they all belong to a particular organization or business, or when they are all going somewhere together.

example.ex: With its own fleet of trucks, the company delivers most orders overnight...
example.tran: 这个公司拥有自己的货车车队，大多数订购货品可以隔日送到。

example.ex: A fleet of ambulances took the injured to hospital.
example.tran: 一队救护车把伤者送往医院。

value.tran: (尤指同一机构或统一行动的)车队

trans: 舰队街，弗利特街(位于伦敦中心的一条街道，曾是全国性大报社所在地)
